Sentencas: Three lanthanum-based perovskite ceramic compounds were studied as contact materials, (La0.8Sr0.2)(0.95)Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-delta (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4034 (LNC), between a Crofer22APU interconnect and a La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 (LSF) cathode.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The layers were deposited using in all cases wet colloidal spray technique.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Phase structures of materials were checked by X-ray Diffraction (XRD) measurements.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity and thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) for these selected compounds were also determined.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The important properties of the resulting [interconnect/contact layer/cathode} systems; including area specific resistance (ASR), reactivity, and adhesion of contact materials to the interconnect and to the cathode were investigated.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the electrical resistance and reactivity of the system without a contact layer, (steel/LSF/LSF) system, was measured for comparison.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The contact resistance is strongly influenced by the conductivity of selected contact materials, showing the lowest ASR values for (Cr0fer22APU/LNC/LSF} assembly.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The point microanalysis on cross-section of the systems, after ASR measurements, reveals that there is chromium enrichment in the contact and cathode layers which allows the formation of phases like SrCr04 and Cr-containing perovskite in short exposure times.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An adequate integrity and low reactivity is achieved when LNF contact coating is applied between Crofer22APU and LSF cathode without compromising the contact resistance of the system.
Titulo: Effects of using (La0.8Sr0.2)0.95Fe0.6Mn0.3Co0.1O3 (LSFMC), LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ (LNF) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3-δ (LNC) as contact materials on solid oxide fuel cells
